OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE YELLOWTAIL DAM MONTANABIG HORN CO. 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE SITE IS ON THE BIGHORN RIVER AT THE BASE OF YELLOWTAIL DAM.  SAMPLES FROM THIS SITE WERE TAKEN DURING A STUDY OF THE POTENTIAL DECLINE IN FISH PRODUCTION OF A NEWLY IMPOUNDED RESERVOIR.  SAMPLING WAS DONE FROM 1968 THROUGH 1970; AND THE RESULTS WERE PUBLISHED IN THE THESIS ""LIMNOLOGICAL STUDIES ON BIGHORN LAKE AND ITS TRIBUTARIES"" BY RAYMOND SOLTERO (MONTANA STATE UNIVERSITY; JUNE 1971).  FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT CHIEF OF RESOURCES AT BIGHORN CANYON NATIONAL RECREATION AREA P.O. BOX 7458 FORT SMITH MONTANA 59035.  TEL (406) 6662412.  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY PAUL MCELVERY AT NPSWRD 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE SUITE 250 FORT COLLINS COLORADO 80525.  TEL (970) 2253516.***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: CLARK FORK RIVER AT GRANT-KOHRS NHS
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION IS LOCATED ON THE DEER LODGE POWELL CO. MT 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE SITE IS WITHIN THE BOUNDARY OF GRANTKOHRS RANCH NATIONAL HISTORIC SITE AND IS LOCATED 2 KILOMETERS DOWNSTREAM FROM A U.S. GEOLOGICAL SURVEY GAGING STATION (NO. 12324200) AT DEER LODGE.  WATER MONITORING AT THIS SITE WAS CONDUCTED HOURLY FOR 46 HOURS IN JULY 1994 AND AGAIN IN FEBRUARY 1995.  THE RESULTS WERE USED IN ""DIEL VARIATION OF TRACE METALS IN THE UPPER CLARK FORK RIVER MONTANA"" (ENVIRON. SCI. TECHNOL. 1996; 30; 19531960) BY CHRISTINE BRICK AND JOHNNIE N. MOORE; DEPARTMENT OF GEOLOGY; UNIVERSITY OF MONTANA MISSOULA; MONTANA.  STAFF GAGE MEASUREMENTS STORED AT THIS STATION WERE ACTUALLY RECORDED AT THE USGS STATION: 12324200 CLARK FORK AT DEER LODGE MT ABOUT 1 MILE UPSTREAM.  FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT THE RESOURCE MANAGEMENT SPECIALIST; GRANTKOHRS RANCH N.H.S.; P.O. BOX 790; DEER LODGE MT 597220790.  DATA UPLOADED TO STORET BY THE NPSWRD; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE; SUITE 250; FT. COLLINS; CO 80525. (TEL. 9702253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

MonitoringLocationName: Gardner River at Rescue Creek Trail Footbridge
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The sample site is located on the Gardner River near the confluence of the Yellowstone River and drains approximately 52,318 hectares of the north and west portions of Yellowstone National Park.  Several portions of the Gardner River's watershed are thermally influenced.  Obsidian Creek, a prominent tributary in the southern portion of the watershed drains several thermal features whose waters are very acidic.  In addition, the Boiling River empties into the Gardner River approximately 2 miles upstream from the sample location and contributes greatly to the dissolved solutes found in the lower portion of the Gardner River.

MonitoringLocationName: Madison River 1.21km West of MT/WY State Boundary
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is located near the Montana/Wyoming state line on the west side of Yellowstone National Park.  The river basin from the sample site encompasses approximately 108,780 hectares and drains much of the west-central portion of Yellowstone National Park.  The Madison River begins at the confluence of the Gibbon and Firehole Rivers both of which receive great amounts of thermal influence.   A USGS gage station is located approximately 1.6 kilometers downstream of the sample site.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Madison River near West Yellowstone, MT
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is located at the Highway 191 crossing of the Madison River, just west of Yellowstone National Park, and approximately 6 km north of West Yellowstone, Montana.  The river basin from the sample site encompasses approximately 109,000 hectares and drains much of the west-central portion of Yellowstone National Park.  The Madison River begins at the confluence of the Gibbon and Firehole rivers both of which receive geothermal influence.  A USGS gaging station (06037500) is located approximately 7.5 km upstream of the sample site. Coordinates (in decimal degrees) for the Hwy 191 bridge crossing of the Madison River are 44.715549, -111.102835 (WGS84). Sampling is conducted from an ATV/jeep trail bridge crossing east of, but paralleling Hwy 191.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is located on the Yellowstone River approximately 9 miles from the north entrance gate of Yellowstone National Park adjacent to highway 87 near the unincorporated town of Corwin Springs, MT.  The site is located near a USGS gage station and is sampled from the bridge that crosses the river.  The watershed encompasses approximately 678,318 hectares and drains much of the northern and eastern portions of Yellowstone National Park.

LOCATION CORRESPONDS TO AQUATICS STATION AQ-2.MAINTAINED FOR AQUATICS AND AS AN UP-GRADIENT STATIONFROM THE CONFLUENCE OF THE BLACKFOOT RIVER WITH HOGUMCREEK.  ASSISTS IN CHARACTERIZATIONOF FLOW AND WATER CHEM FROM THE SEVEN-UP PETEAREA.
MAINTAINED TO DETECT CONTAMINATION FROM THE BOUMA POLEYARD.
SAMPLING STATION MAINTAINED TO PROVIDES DATA ONLANDERS FORK WATER CHEMISTRY UP-GRADIENT FROM THECONFLUENCE WITH COPPER CREEK.

CORRESPONDS TO AQUATICS STATION AQ-11.ON THE BLACKFOOT RIVER APPROX 3 MIUP-GRADIENT OF PERMIT BOUNDARY.  BASELINECONDITIONS ARE DIFFICULT TO MONITORUP-GRADIENT OF THE PROJECT DUE TO THE PRESENCE OF AMARSH/SWAMP COMPLEX.
CORRESPONDS TO AQUATICS STATION AQ-3.  MAINTAINED TOCHARACTERIZE INFLUENCE FROM HOGUM CREEK ON THE FLOW ANDOVERALL WATER CHEMISTRY ON THE BLACKFOOT RIVER.

SAMPLING STATION CORRESPONDS TO AQUATICS STATION AQ-17.STATION LOCATED ON COPPER CREEK APPROXIMATELY 2.0MILES UP-GRADIENT OF PERMIT BOUNDARY.  STATIONDETERMINES THE INFLUENCE OF COPPER CREEKON THE WATER CHEMISTRY/QUANTITY IN LANDERSFORK.

STATION IS LOCATED ON THE LANDERS FORK 500 FEETUP-GRADIENT FROM THE CONFLUENCE OF THE BLACKFOOT RIVERAND LANDERS FORK.MAINTAINED TO DETERMINE THE CONTRIBUTION OF LANDERS FORK ONTHE BLACKFOOT RIVER AND THE CONTRIBUTION OF THE LANDFILL.
SAMPLING STATION IS LOCATED BETWEEN SAMPLING STATIONSSP-SW-34.L AND SP-SW-15.L TO PROVIDE DATA FOR THIS> 2.5 MILE STRETCH OF LANDERS FORK WHICH PASSESTHROUGH MINERALIZED ZONES.

THIS SAMPLING STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BECAUSE OF THEDISTANCE BETWEEN STATIONS SP-SW-40.B AND SP-SW-16.B,APPROXIMATELY TWO MILES.  THIS STATION WILL PROVIDEADDITIONAL WATER CHEMISTRY DATA FOR THE BLACKFOOTRIVER.
THIS SAMPLING STATION WILL PROVIDE INFORMATION ONWATER CHEMISTRY FROM A TRIBUTARY UP-GRADIENT FROM THEPERMIT BOUNDARY.
